---
title: Fresh Mozz Toasts with Guac & Tomato with Arugula Salad & Balsamic Drizzle
description: It’s lunchtime at your villa nestled in the hills among olive orchards and vineyards. You’ve only got time for a quick lunch before you get back to tending the grapes, so it’ll be a simple but tasty open-faced affair. Spread toasted sourdough slices with guacamole and a sprinkle of chili flakes, top with fresh mozzarella and juicy seasoned tomatoes, then drizzle with a tangy-sweet balsamic glaze to bring it all home. On the side, an arugula salad sprinkled with Parmesan keeps it light for the afternoon ahead—bocce ball, anyone?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/fresh-mozz-toasts-with-guac-tomato-24bed0b3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/646465cbd0c978f47f04b2bb.pdf
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
nutrition:
  calories: 460 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 17 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 980 mg
servings: 2
time required: 10 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/fresh-mozz-toasts-with-guac-and-tomato-646465cbd0c978f47f04b2bb
cuisine: Italian
---

Toast @sourdough bread{2%slices}. Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounces} into rounds. Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @arugula{2%ounces}, @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoons}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season lightly with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread @guacamole{1/2%cup} onto toasted bread. Season with salt, pepper, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}. Top with mozzarella and seasoned tomato.

Halve toasts on a diagonal; divide toasts and salad between #plates{}. Drizzle everything with as much @balsamic glaze{5%teaspoons} as you like. Serve.